      ],
      "created_at": "2026-05-30T12:00:13.655098+00:00",
      "last_escalated_size": 3,
      "last_escalated_at": "2026-05-30T18:43:50.378578+00:00",
      "picks_file": "picks/picks-2026-05-30-1844.md",
      "why_text": "The surprise box office performance of a film based on a creepypasta internet myth is sending a loud signal to Hollywood: niche online lore has a ravenous, built-in audience that studios keep underestimating. The Backrooms \u2014 a liminal horror concept born from a single 2019 4chan post and turbocharged by YouTube \u2014 has now outperformed films with far bigger budgets and IP recognition. This is less about one film and more about a generation that grew up with internet mythology treating it with the same reverence older audiences gave Stephen King.",
